caption: The food is really good
Great service! I walked in, ordered mango sticky rice to go. It was delicious! Will be going back there to try out something out in the rest of their menu!

A serious contender for my favorite Thai food in the DMV area. If you like me can't get enough green thai curry with fried tofu and mixed veggies, I'd seriously suggest you check this restaurant out. They get the flavor just right.
Amazing food!! Service is great. Not from the area, but stop by whenever I can. The pork belly is amazing 🤩. And so is everything I have had. Been coming back for a few years now.
Best green curry ever. I recently moved out of DC and this is what i miss most. Also amazing drunken noodles.
If you loved spicy foods then this is the place.  Great foods  and good service!

The food is good! They have heaters if you wanna seat outside. Everything was pretty clean. The spices were good. The spring roll's crust was crunchy. The food came fast. You can check the menu through QR code :) I had the yellow curry and my friend had a pad thai. Both portions were big. We left there pretty satisfied.  Final price: $48 for 2 appetizers + 2 entrees + taxes
Great place for thai food and hang out! Try the Panag Curry!!!
great food and staff

The absolute worst place in mount pleasant. I have kept going back out of being nice and their close proximity to me. Tonight was about the 8th time. The staff are rude , unfriendly, food portions keep getting smaller.  Tonight she gave me the wrong food and instead of fixing it she was arguing with me when she was clearly wrong. Will never  set foot at their place again.    Horrible from every aspect

I ordered Spicy noodle soup it kind of sweet, and salty. I'm not sure if they put MSG in it because I feel so thirsty within 30 mins to 3 hours after I ate. The price is too high for noodle in my opinion. I still have to order Drunken noodle afterward.
One of my favorite spots to eat. excellent location, well kept, and excellent customer service. Very good job!
Delicious, though the portion size is a bit on the small side for the price compared to other restaurants. Still tasty, though!

Ordered for delivery. My curry was $17 and I barely got a half full container of it, mostly chicken, hardly any sauce. When I added the rice it soaked up what little sauce there was and made it very dry. Definitely not worth the money for what I got. I'll pass on ordering from here again. 🙁
Ordered at the entrance, waited outside, had my food in 15 minutes. Sweet!
Great location, great service and great food.  It's a trifecta!  I loved the shrimp roll and the drunken noodles.  I would definitely come back again.
Horrible experience. Would rather go anywhere else than here. Bad staff
Portions are small for the price. Very few pieces of meat/veggie in the curry. The curry is also pretty sweet and bland. The Tom kha soup is delicious though.
This spot is good! Good pricing, considerable portions and the employees are constantly kind.

This has been one of our favorite places since moving here last year. Tonight pretty much erased that.  This is two part: One on Caviar and one one the restaurant because that’s the provider THEY CHOOSE, and their rude manager hung up on me when I asked about having an order remade.  We placed an order at 6:40pm and a 30-40 min deliver window was provided to us.  It’s now 7:57pm and our order hasn’t been picked up.  I called once at 7:25 to verify our order was ready and the person who answered said it had been ready 10-15min (since around 7:15)  I attempted to contact Caviar/Doordash CX via web, app and twitter to no avail. It seems to be down.  Still no “Dasher” assigned.  I called back at 7:45 when our order was 1 hour out and had been sitting for 30 min.  Put on my Karen hat and asked for the manager. He straight up lied when I asked if they could remake the order and told me the food had only been sitting for 10 min.  Then told me I could come pick it up but they wouldn’t remake it, honestly that part IS on them. They CHOOSE the platform for delivery.  He hung up on me and here we are. 8:03 got the notification that food has been picked up and that the driver is near...which is impossible.  Hour old pad Thai is gross, and would have been considered “dead in the window” at a restaurant. It would never or should never be served!  It sits at the bar, out of temp for and hour? That’s a call to the Health Dept.  Sure things are difficult but that doesn’t give folks a pass on CX.
Great. Fast and efficient.

I just called to place an order for (2) Larb Gai @ $5 each and Red Curry Duck $11 dinner, of which, is stated on their menu listed above.  The staff said your total is $34.95.  The price on the menu are wrong.  The Larb Gai is $8 each and the Red Curry Duck is $15.99.  He wouldn’t the missed print.  I wouldn’t recommend spending your money at this location. Poor Customer Service skills.

My favorite place to get Thai takeout in DC!  The food is delicious 😋, every time. I always order a few items because I can never decide on a favorite. Their pumpkin curry in the fall is my go-to order when it's available, but the rest of the year I will order pad see ew, green curry, drunken noodles, and duck rolls.

This restaurant hands down had the most COVID-19 precaution measures for dine in. They took our temperature when we arrive. Had a QR code to view the menu and disposable cups, water bottle and silverware. Tables were spaced out as well. Staff wore masks and shields and were super friendly. Food was delicious!!!
Excellent duck curry!  Wouldn't change a thing.
Great food. Nice neighborhood. Very friendly staff. They're currently open for dine in with all the precautions. Also have a take out option.
Will never be back. Food was not fresh and tasty. Could not even finish.
Usually my go to neighborhood spot but got food poisoning after a takeout order the other day.
My friends and i love this place. Its consistently delicious and whenever i try a new dish i’m pleased! Big foodie so i dont say this lightly!

We love Thai food and ordered takeout tofu drunken noodles and tofu panang curry.  Pros: flavor was great. The noodles were cooked a little more than we're used to, but it tasted great. Panang curry was well done too. It had a good amount of citrus that wasn't overpowering.  Cons: We were hoping for a larger portion of noodles and brown rice. Brown rice was $2 more, so it was upsetting to run out of rice before curry. Also, Panang curry only had tofu, no vegetables. We've usually gotten bell peppers/carrots from other restaurants.  Still, would recommend.
Food is immaculate I’d eat it everyday if I could
Great local Thai restaurant in Mount Pleasant. The food and staff are amazing. I’ve been going for years and have never had a bad experience - including take out.  Please make sure to support them.

BeauThai in Mt Pleasant is my favorite Thai restaurant in DC (and the Shaw location is great, too)! The atmosphere at both are great & their food is always outstanding. My favorite is the Shrimp Pad Thai but I enjoy several of their other entree’s. The service is quick & friendly, and the prices are very reasonable. The owners do a great job at hiring managers, chefs & staff that really show a passion for 5 Star Service & delicious Thai food in a very well-run establishment. I highly recommend BeauThai to anyone looking for the best Thai food in DC! Great work, Team BeauThai! Keep it up!
Yummy Yummy Yummy!
Average American-Thai food. However, the mango sticky rice is the best I’ve had since Thailand. I would go back just for that.
Good Thai food for reasonable prices. The curry and noodles are especially good. The waitstaff is fast and friendly. All around, it's a decent experience.
The food was delicious!

This BT location has the most efficient staff in the history of restaurants! I went on a Tuesday evening and was amazed by how attentive they were with refilling water and turning over tables. They were also helpful and friendly. I love BT because of how many vegetarian and vegan options they have - I had the drunken noodles with tofu which was perfect, and the eggplant in garlic sauce which was well cooked by slightly too oily for my taste. I always get takeout from this location so it was nice to dine in for a change, and all in all I'll be back and hopefully sit on the outside patio to take in everything Mount Pleasant has to offer.
Great food and service!
Very good! The green curry with chicken was spicy- watch out for the peppers!
Everything was good, but the drunken noodles were spectacular.
Great food at reasonable prices. Probably my favorite Thai restaurant in DC. Kudos for having Port City Optimal Wit on tap and cold, very cold. :)

We love Beau Thai! Great, quick service. It’s very dangerous that we live in walking distance. We have to practice a lot of self control to not eat here everyday. We also enjoy getting take out from here and it’s always quality. My personal favorite is the pineapple fried rice. But everything is delicious.

Nice atmosphere, apart from 2 TVs above the bar which are really distracting and don’t really fit the vibe. Great attentive service. Food was tasty but nothing extraordinary. The Beau Thai chicken special was the stand-out dish. Green curry and Pad Thai were nice too. Spring rolls were bland and served with a sweet sauce (no chilli). Eggplant was too sweet too. A nice place to eat but they could serve up more authentic Thai flavours.
Only tried the duck noodle soup but it was awesome. Reasonable prices for DC. Great service, lol my water never got below half a glass. Definitely worth checking out.

It takes a lot for me to leave a 5 star review, because I’m really judgmental when it comes to food. But the food here was AMAZING. And for the price, it’s cheap. Which makes it even better. I just wanted to try everything on the menu! We got the pork belly appetizer, as well as duck rolls or something and ka pao. It was all  perfection. Looking forward to coming here again

The best luck of my first years in DC was living down the street from the original Beau Thai at 5th and NJ in Shaw. I now live in Mt. Pleasant and it is as much of a staple meal. Vegetarians: Get the drunken noodles with tofu 🤤
Beau Thai is a reliable place for great Thai. Super fast service, affordable, and it’s a huge spot so you can pretty much guarantee you’ll get a seat as a walk-in even on a busy night.
Really interesting ingredient combos, but everything works! Creative cocktails and delicious food.
Delicious, but needs more vegan options, especially curry.
Great service and better food
Great!
Some of the best curry I've had in DC and generally overall as well. I also loved their duck noodles, super rich and delicious! Cannot wait to come back here!

Be prepared to wait for 30+ minutes for your food after the instructed pick up time and be harrassed by the bartender while you wait. Placed an order for pick up at 7:50, was told it would be ready at 8:20. I show up to at 8:20 to grab my order and told it will be 5 more minutes. At 8:40 I still have no food and people are coming in and picking up orders that were placed almost 30 minutes after mine. When I wanted to know why my order was taking so long the bartender was sarcastic and rude, encouraging other patrons to make fun of me. Finally got my order 30 minutes after I was told it was going be ready and  management didn't care how I was being treated by staff or other customers.
The food wasn’t bad, just a little sweet. More like Americanized Thai than traditional Thai food.
Amazing service and yummy food, thank you!

I’ve become stingy with my Google 5-Star reviews, but Beau Thai gets it.  The service, at 3pm on a Sunday, was probably the best that I have received in DC.  Granted, they were not crazy busy, but still.  And the food was well above average at below average prices.  We had the papaya salad, drunken noodles and Thai sausage.  Each was great.  The iced coffee and iced tea were both great.
Spicy Jungle Curry was delicious as were the pumpkin empenados.
Wow, a real gem. Great food for a great price. Very polite service as well.
Yummy and spicy but I’m not so much a fan of the spicy...
My favorite neighborhood Thai place in my favorite neighborhood in DC
Best Thai restaurant, nice ambiance and excellent food.
Very spicy and delicious food. No paranormal activity detected. Still might be haunted.
Great food, fast and friendly service.
Cute space with tons of seating both inside and outside. Huge servings on the pad Thai
Went here for lunch with some co-workers. Chill atmosphere, nice decor, delicious food, and super nice staff.
Pleasant little spot for some quick Thai comfort food.
This is my neighborhood go to. I eat at this restaurant more than any other sir in Mt Pleasant and Columbia Heights. They beef pad see ew and the panang chicken are off the hook.
Everything was great.
I paid $7 for these two little empanadas and $9 for a pretty sad, overdressed papaya salad (two shrimp). Have had a good experience with their entrees, but this was very disappointing.

I want to like it more, but everything on the menu is always a little too sweet. It's definitely geared towards an American palate, but there could still be less sugar overall and more spice and depth of flavor. The people there are very nice, though.
This place is one my favorite Thai spots to go to. The food is amazing. The service is just spectacular I haven’t gone anywhere that takes care of you like this place.
Nice location and the food is amazing!!
Reliably delicious, pleasant atmosphere, wonderful staff.
Wonderful service, delicious inexpensive food, good happy hour deals! What’s not to like, the place is truly a gem.
Great food. Friendly staff. Never too long of a wait

Our go to Thai, we eat here almost every other week. Staff is very friendly and nice. It has such a  welcoming feeling as soon as you walk in. The food is great, had just about every dish on the menu.
Noodle bowls are awesome. Waitstaff are friendly and prompt.
Their Pad Thai is always juicy, never dry!
Probably you’re best option for a hip dinner in Mt. Pleasant. Fairly good food, fairly good prices.
Green curry is delicious
Delicious but spicy
Some of the best yellow veggie curry ever!

I wouldn't know where to start with this place. Every experience has been consistently outstanding. Point your finger at random on any food item, unless you have a dietary restriction, you're going to enjoy yourself.
Love this place! Good variety of food and the service is great! If you're looking for something different.. Try the homemade Ginger Beer!
Thai coffee and yellow curry; yum!
Great food quality

Decent place for a quick bite, but not one where you want to sit for a while. The vegetarian/vegan options were very limited- for a Thai restaurant in 2019 that is surprising. The chopsticks were the wooden takeout type - huh? Get some real chopsticks. Food tasted fine but I was hoping for a bit more than that. Service was attentive if a touch overbearing.
Its good foof
excellent!! 👍🏿👍🏿

Great service and outstanding food! We would definitely choose to eat here again, next time we're in the city. The atmosphere is great and they were very accommodating of kids and large family groups. For a busy Sunday we were impressed with how quickly we were in and out!
Food was delicious, service was fast, price was unbeatable!
Friendly staff and great food. Always a wonderful experience
(Translated by Google) Rich dishes!  (Original) Ricos platos!
(Translated by Google) Very good food and attention  (Original) Muy buena comida y atencion
Great place especially for a catered event :)
Great food and Mount Pleasant is a really nice area. I would recommend it!

Went here for a bite to eat as part of a bridal party after shopping for bridesmaid dresses all morning. This was a pretty good Thai place. The Thai tea was tasty, and the level of spice was pretty good. We had a large party, and only two people’s order weren’t prefect, and it’s just because the spice levels were swapped. They fixed it right away. The staff was friendly, and the inside was just precious. I would definitely recommend this place!
Excellent neighborhood spot! The noodle bowls are a must try!
Super cute restaurant with great food. The staff is always great and suggests different options.
Great food. Great price. Good service. The lady was very nice. I forgit her name but left here 20% tip.
Lobsters were good. And Rose wine even better
Fast service and great food!

The food we ordered was delicious.  I ordered the classic shrimp pad tai, and it tasted delicious.   Only complaints are lack of parking common with all restaurants in the area and the automatic tip of 20% tacked on the bill with a group of 6.  Service was good, but not 20% good.  Tables were wobbly, and we spilled our drinks multiple times.
Hot and spicy noodle soup
Good Thai food.
Smells great tastes awful
Great food
Needs a better happy hour.
So glad my favorite joint opened a new location in mount pleasant
Excellent food and service!

Our absolute favorite, we go to or order from Beau Thai at least once a week. The owners are awesome, the staff is great, and the food is out of this world. The hot and spicy noodle bowl = one of the great joys of this life.
I've enjoyed the soups here every time

I was very (mt)pleasantly surprised with my experience at Beau Thai last week. We arrived at the restaurant somewhat on the later end, but that didn't detract from the quality of service. The menu is clean and seems to cover all the classics that are requisite for a Thai joint popular amongst millennials. Because it was my first time there, I stuck with the pad thai and greatly enjoyed it. The late hours and wide variety of cocktails makes this a great addition to the food scene in DC.

Not all that. The ambiance was nice. Everything went smooth until I got my food. No utensil, no napkin, no soy sauce. The owner sat there beside us, he never acknowledged us, or offered to lend a helping hand. Even when he heard about our grievances. I was over it, won't be going back
Food was really good, service was attentive and it wasn’t overly loud.

Claudia Crane here (somehow husband's account came up). I told the waiter the chicken noodle bowl had too much sugar. She offered more soy sauce; I felt that wouldn't help. The menu said the chicken was simmered in broth; it's texture was of not very tender roast chicken with sweet broth poured on. This place used to be better, but it seems they've gone cheap with soy and sugar as flavoring like so many Chinese restaurants these days.
Delicious food, neighborhood vibe
Their dumplings were delicious. They also have very friendly staff and manager. I would eat here again.
Clean and nice atmosphere...polite and quick service

(Translated by Google) Large and somewhat soulless place but with very good food. The curries are delicious and the papaya salad good. Highly recommended  (Original) Local grande y algo desangelado pero con muy buena comida. Los currys están ricos y la ensalada de papaya  buena. Muy recomendable

Vegan friendly and lovely to sit outside in Mt Pleasant on a spring evening. We were delighted to find out we were inadvertantly supporting "Dining Out for Life" tonight at this place. The server seemed rushed to get our plates from us.
Go-to Thai place in DC. Great drink and beer selection and good food!
The place is nice and the food is very good.
Nice space for a relaxed dinner with our family. Service and food were good but not nearly the best Thai we’ve had.
Good
Ginger shrimp special was great

I love this place for our local go to restaurant on Mt. Pleasant Ave. Lively atmosphere during high times. A touch of contemporary industrial accents and nostalogia. Check out the floor. Decent, long bar for drinking and dining. The Drunken Noodles is a favorite dish for me. Good full flavors. Nice balance of meat and noodles. Lots of bowls on the menu with ample broth. Question the amount of sodium in broth dishes. But all the meats have been tender and savory. This Beau Thai has been consistent and dependable at delivering tasty drinks and meals. The same for Carry Out too.
Great neighborhood gem

Great Thai food, great service, nice ambiance. My wife had a fantastic cocktail and the yellow curry. I had the Beau chicken, which was excellent- crispy, spicy, and full of mingling flavors. The kids had appetizers for their meals. The peanut chicken was good, but the 'empanadas' were a bit plain. We finished up with mango sticky rice, which was quite good.
Great Thai food. Good menu with more than your standard Thai menu. Great bar also.

This may sound crazy and there may be no scientific proof but the "Hot And Spicy Noodle Bowl" has CURED two of my colds.  Seriously.  I went in  with a cold, had this, and woke up the next day cured.  No symptoms.  Can't explain it but I think they may have cured the common cold.
Friendly staff, somewhat unique menu over standard Thai cuisine.
Great seasonal Curry with lots of veggies. Friendly and efficient staff.
Good service and delicious food :)
Love their drunken noodles
The food was delicious, the price was right, and the staff were delightfully attentive. Perfect for a relaxed dinner! The ambiance was lovely as well.
Good food. Friendly staff. Surprisingly good brunch. Will go again!
Always delicious. Service is good.
Great happy hour!

Modern and casual ambiance along with tasty, moderately priced food. I've dined in and had food delivered and have enjoyed every order, from the appetizers (rolls, calamari) to noodles (pad thai, pad see ew) to curry entrees and fried rice. I've had more flavorful Thai food elsewhere, but this is one my favorite places to go in DC.
Worth it.
Great food, decent prices!
Great duck noodles, really great good with great service!
Amazing food! If you like spicy curry, try the red one :)

Very friendly service, best Thai I've had in DC for Pad Se Ew & Pad Thai. Amazing steamed dumplings! They deliver after 5:30, worth waiting if you want delivery but the restaurant is very nice and spacious!
Great food and friendly, attentive service. They do staple dishes well, but their curries and signature dishes are so good.

Sat outside to enjoy the balmy late afternoon and the people-watching. Attentive, professional, and friendly service. The spring rolls, papaya salad, and steamed dumplings were all really good. The duck rolls were outstanding. We were eating early and hadn't noticed the happy hour notice, but enjoyed a good kiwi sauvignon blanc for $18.
Delicious!!
Nice spot in Mt. Pleasant in D.C.  for good Thai.

This is not real Thai by any means. We ordered 4 plates, they brought us 5 claiming we ordered the fifth plate. The waiter did not confirm before placing final order. The masaman noodle bowl had chicken pieces that felt like eating raw meat. The pad Thai my wife ordered was very sweet with lot of high fructose corn syrup. The fried rice my other friend ordered was equally sweet and we did not enjoy the dinner at all. Look elsewhere if you are after real Thai taste.
I eat a lot of thai food and this was the tastiest thai food I've ever had. Fast service, decent prices. I will be coming back next time I'm in DC.
Love the panang curry. Sticky rice with mango dessert is so yummy.
It's a good local spot with decent happy hour specials.
We had some really good Thai food over here! The curries are delicious.
Awesome Pad Se Ew.  The spiked Thai tea was very interesting and very spicy.
Good lunch with shrimp toast and Thai ice coffee. Attentive staff.
Good food
Great food, fair prices, interesting atmosphere
Our favorite restaurant in the neighborhood! Recommend the Beau Thai Chicken, or the Drunken Noodles w/ Tofu for vegetarians. They've got vegetarian and gluten free menus upon request if you need.
Great food!!
Really nice food, varied yet authentic menu, fast service and seductive decor make for an all - round high quality, casual dining experience.
great food
Delicious and authentic papaya salad, just like in Bangkok. The vast majority of the other dishes were very good.
One of the best Thai restaurants in DC.  Try the noodle bowls,  whole fish,  fried rice for kids.
My favorite restaurant in Mount Pleasant! Lovely atmosphere, delicious food, and great happy hour. Get the empanadas.. you won't be disappointed :)
Good Thai food. The place is nice too. I went during the winter time and it was chilly inside the place. Good for carry out
Pad sse wu and red curry are so good

I took my friend there for dinner and we're completely ignored very nice place but the service suck.other around us got service it were like we were invisible finally the manager came over and gave us a suck apologize like we were the problem.
Good place

Very good food, but not a great date spot. Nothing wrong with the service or the food - it's very good, and the place has a full bar. Issue with dates is it is cafeteria style seating on a hard concrete floor. Not exactly romantic. But what they lack in ambiance, they put into the kitchen. I'd go back.
Good food and great service. Great place to go with a baby, enough place for strollers.
Excellent Thai food!

Sadly, I have to give Beau Thai Mt Pleasant a 1 star. We have been ordering from them for a couple years and have had good food and service until now. After ordering the dinner size entree of sauteed vegetables, we received an appetizer sized box of barely cooked vegetables in a watery "sauce". The box was also filled half way with tofu which was not in the description on the menu. We called and spoke to the manager to express confusion about the size of the portion received and the quality of the dish. He told us that we must not have ordered from them recently because they have reduced the sizes of their portions and increased prices! He then decided to question our expertise on vegetable entrees because according to him, this was made with high quality ingredients and is a standard way of preparing the dish. Neither of these answers were helpful or remotely apologetic and we will not be ordering from them again.
Pad see ew was delicious and wonderfully authentic. It was expensive though.
I like the food in this restaurant has a great taste for that I give five star
Great Thai food and nice wines. Attentive and friendly service and an overall pleasant experience. Definitely one of the better restaurants in Mt. Pleasant!
Tasty affordable Thai food. Quite large.
Great food and quick lunch service

Service was bad, waitress was behaving as if she was annoyed with us ordering. Ordered yellow curry and it could've been better,  the tofu was bland so I'll probably take my food home and season it myself. Asked the waitress to pack my food, waited 20 minutes (we were the only customers there) then approached her and the group of waitresses conversing to ask for my food. Apparently it had been packed for a while now she just didn't find it necessary to give it back to me. Don't know how this place was rated 4.4 stars I'm extremely disappointed
Must try the Beau Thai chicken, didn't have a great bar experience though.
I walked in for the first time and was greeted promptly. The aroma of Thai food was very pleasant. Service is very fast.
Good food and service.
Basic Thai place, done well and not overpriced or pretentious
Pretty good food. Service was great. Very delicious food.
Decent Thai in pleasant atmosphere. Nothing to write home about.
Brilliant food, I had the Red Curry Duck which was a little spicy, but just what I wanted. Staff is friendly and outdoor seating very pleasant in the summer.
Fabulous Thai food in Mt. Pleasant...Kapow is my favorite.
My favorite affordable Thai place in the city.  Try the Beau Thai Chicken. All the currys and standard Thai dishes are also good.  Some decent happy hour options as well.
Excellent service!

Came here because of the reviews here and the reviews are obviously planted.  Steamed dumplings were mushy typical supermarket shui mai.  'Beau Thai chicken' was General Tso. Not joking -  avoid it unless you want a comfort food thing.  And even then,  skip it.
Good Pad Thai
Had the duck noodle bowl, excellent!

(Translated by Google) Fast service, good food and reasonable prices. Of how many dishes we have tried I would recommend the Pad Thai and the different varieties of curry; red for those who enjoy spicy and green, much softer, for those who prefer it in small doses. Papaya salad, on the other hand, has been poor and scarce in quantity. The portions are not too large, perfect for a first and second course. With a single plate to eat, one could stay hungry. The service has been agile, fast. They have not known or wanted, however, to answer what one of the desserts consisted of.  (Original) Servicio rápido, buena comida y precios razonables. De cuantos platos hemos probado recomendaría el Pad Thai y las diferentes variedades de curry; la roja para quien disfrute con el picante y la verde, mucho más suave, para quienes lo preferimos en pequeñas dosis. La ensalada de papaya, en cambio, me ha resultado pobre y escasa en cantidad. Las raciones no son demasiado grandes, perfecta para tomarse un primer y segundo plato. Con un único plato para comer, uno pudiera quedarse con hambre. El servicio ha sido ágil, rápido. No han sabido o querido, sin embargo, respondernos en que consistía uno de los postres.

Beau Thai is probably the best Thai restaurant in DC. Everything is good, but I can particularly vouch for the pad thai, every variety of curry, and the drunken noodles. I recommend the empanadas for an appetizer.  So you know, they dial back the spicy on phone orders - so if you want it Thai hot just ask. This reviewer likes to sweat while he eats, so take that for what it's worth.

In my 20s, I went to O'Tasty on Columbia Road, but now that I'm 30, I graduated to Beau Thai. It's a beautiful restaurant on Mt. Pleasant Street and offers many seats. The food is a step up from your usual Thai restaurant, but with the familiar taste of the Thai food you know. The green chicken curry is AMAZING and fills you up. Also, they only use fresh mango on their sticky rice and mango. Wow.
Great modern take on Thai food with other fusion options thrown in. Loved the food, and very cool atmosphere.
Good atmosphere and great food. Try the hot and spicy bowl and the spicy spiked beau Thai tea
Drunken noodles are tremendous!
Quick service and amazing food. Prices are very reasonable to top it off!
A good and reliable thai place. I've carried out and eaten in and have always enjoyed my food. I also really appreciate that they will leave the fish sauce out of certain dishes upon request.
username: M U K T I . D E S A I

caption: Very boring as far as Thai food goes. I prefer the carryout space up the street (zabver). It has good value but not much more.

One of my favorite places in DC. The food is awesome, the atmosphere feels clean and modern, the prices are reasonable, and the service is very speedy. The curries are awesome, and they have good variety of other interesting entrees and appetizers. I visit regularly for both dine-in and take-out. My only complaint may be that they've packed a lot of tables into a small space, but they have plenty of staff to cover them, and because there are so many tables with fast turnover, there never seems to a wait.

I go to this Beau Thai several times a month and always get the tofu pad thai.  The curries and spring rolls are also good, but I really go here for the noodles. The outdoor dining can be nice when the weather is good, but I generally sit inside or order in.

My program director generously treated us to lunch (delivery) this past week. Taste wise - my shrimp in Penang curry with brown rice was delicious! I saved the leftover curry sauce and ate it with my own cooking. However, I was surprised at how tiny the portion it came in. There were no veggies (not even onion? peppers?) - just 7 shrimp swimming in a cup of curry sauce. For $13 dollars, I expected to feel at least as if I did eat? Maybe I need to order two entrees next time.
I love this low-key neighborhood place. It's not fancy nor sophisticated, but it is definitely consistent and yummy. The curry -all of them- are delicious and the staff is friendly and kind.
The best.
Great Pad Thai and Thai iced tea. Great decor and friendly staff.

Not the best Thai food I've had but certainly up there. Best I've had in DC. Delicious noodle bowls and yummy curries. Very affordable at $10-$15 a plate. Come on the weekend for their creative Thai brunches and you won't be disappointed (try the Hangover Special).
